<TITLE> Sheikh Helal gets bail </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 12 (bdnews24.com)The High Court Monday granted bail to former Awami League lawmaker Sheikh Helal, his wife Rupa Chowdhury, and the wife and daughter of AL lawmaker Lotus Kamal, Kasmiri and Kasdi Kamal. Two separate HC division benches granted bail in separate corruption cases. A HC bench of justices Md Muzammel Hossain and Md. Afzal Hossain Ahmed granted Sheikh Helal bail for three months in two cases, on for amassing illegal wealth and the other an extortion case. The court also stayed the proceedings in the cases for 3 months and ordered the government to show cause within four weeks why the proceedings should not be quashed. Trial courts sentenced him for 13 years and 7 years respectively in the two cases. The same HC bench granted bail to his wife Rupa Chowdhury for 2 months in a case for abetting her husband in amassing illegal wealth, in which the lower court sentenced her to 3 years. Another HC bench of justices Mirza Hossain Haider and Shamim Hasnain granted bail to Kasmiri Kamal and Kasdi Kamal in a corruption case filed by the Anticorruption Commission. Barrister Amir Ul Islam moved for Sheikh Helal and his wife and Barrister Rafiq Ul Haq appeared for Kasmiri and Kasdi Kamal. bd
